---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

// Home — reassurance, a brief hint of what's here, an invitation.
// Story details live on /about; packages on /services.
---

<BaseLayout
  description="Yellow Legal Pad — financial coaching with Stacey. A quiet conversation, without judgment."
>
  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="welcome-heading">
    <div class="column">
      <h1 id="welcome-heading">
        The welcome mat is out.
      </h1>
      <p>
        If money feels complicated, or embarrassing, or just hard to
        look at, you don't need to know anything beforehand to start.
      </p>
      <p>
        Yellow Legal Pad is a small practice run by Stacey. She helps
        people, couples, and families think about money calmly. She
        doesn't sell financial products, and she won't pressure you
        about anything.
      </p>
      <p>
        The name comes from Stacey's grandfather, Grampy. He'd sit at
        the kitchen table with anyone who asked and walk through their
        numbers on a yellow legal pad until the numbers stopped feeling
        scary. <a href="/about">More about Stacey</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="column">
      <p>
        Most financial advice begins by suggesting you've fallen behind.
        Stacey doesn't. The people who come here aren't financially
        unintelligent. They're financially underserved &mdash; by an
        industry that talks past them, charges too much, and assumes they
        should already know.
      </p>
      <p>
        Stacey starts somewhere else: a real conversation, in plain
        language, about your actual life. Whatever's in front of you
        now is what we work with.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="invite-heading">
    <div class="column">
      <h2 id="invite-heading">If you'd like to talk</h2>
      <p>
        Discovery Calls are free and take about twenty minutes. No
        script, no slideshow. Stacey will listen, ask a few questions,
        and say honestly whether she can help. There's no pressure
        to keep going.
      </p>
      <p>
        The best time to start was when Grampy was sitting at the kitchen
        table. The second best time is today.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
        <a href="/contact">Book a Discovery Call</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
